By Sandra Umeh Lagos – The Police in Lagos have charged a 37-years-old man, Ikechukwu Mba, in an Ojo Magistrates’ court in Lagos for allegedly stealing Wall Bracket lights valued N700,000. The defendant is standing trial on two counts of conspiracy and stealing. He, however, pleaded not guilty to the charges pending before Magistrate Mr A.A Adesanya. The prosecutor, Insp. Simon Uche, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on Aug. 13 at the Alaba International Market. He said that the defendant and others, now at large, stole 10 cartons of wall bracket lights from the warehouse of one Friday Nnamani, the complainant. The prosecutor further told the court that the defendant was arrested and charged, following police investigations. He said that the offence contravened the provisions of Sections 287 and 411 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State 2015. Adesanya granted the defendant bail in the sum of N250, 000 with two sureties in like sum and adjourned the case until Feb. 18, 2020 for mention. (NAN)